車站原初位於{{link-en|科特蘭街 (曼哈頓)|Cortlandt Street (Manhattan)|科特蘭街}}及[[格林尼治街|格林尼治街]]地下，[[曼哈頓下城|曼哈頓下城]]一個外號「{{link-en|無線電高台|Radio Row}}」的地方，該處街道有許多電子儀器販賣<ref name=":3">{{cite web | title=Lost and Found Sound: The Stories | website=NPR | date=February 14, 2002 | url=https://www.npr.org/programs/lnfsound/stories/020603.radiorow.html | access-date=September 15, 2017 | archive-date=2006-10-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061018014921/http://www.npr.org/programs/lnfsound/stories/020603.radiorow.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。該站設有標準的兩個[[側式月台|側式月台]]和兩條軌道<ref name="tracks">{{NYCS const|trackref|trackbook3}}</ref>。車站1965年第一次翻新前，月台牆壁上曾經有由{{link-en|斯奎爾·J·維克斯|Squire J. Vickers}}設計、描繪船隻的馬賽克裝飾<ref name=":8">{{Cite web|url=http://nytm.pastperfectonline.com/webobject/4CDB5840-7230-41E3-B90E-352018180708|title=Terra cotta hexagonal plaque and tile border removed from the Cortlandt Street Station in the 1970s.|date=1918-05-03|website=nytm.pastperfectonline.com|access-date=2018-09-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180906195452/https://nytm.pastperfectonline.com/webobject/4CDB5840-7230-41E3-B90E-352018180708 |archive-date=2018-09-06}}</ref>。紅色的工字樑柱在兩個月台排開，每隔一柱就有標準的黑底白字的站名牌，交替顯示「科特蘭街」和「世界貿易中心」<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?222|title=IRT Cortlandt St/WTC station looking south along southbound platform|last=|first=|date=September 28, 2001|website=nycsubway.org|publisher=New York City Transit|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411005209/https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?222|archive-date=2021-04-11|dead-url=no|access-date=September 7, 2018}}</ref>。
[[File:WTC_Hub_September_2016_vc.png|thumb]]
重建的車站位於格林尼治街地下，與原初車站相同<ref>{{NYCS const|trackref}}</ref><ref name="MTA 2018" />。車站繼承了雙軌雙側式月台的配置，位於地面以下{{Convert|20|ft|m}}<ref name="MTA 2018" /><ref name=":4" /><ref name="nypost september 2011" />。軌道之間仍有樑柱，但車站北端跨過[[世界貿易中心車站_(PATH)|世界貿易中心交通樞紐]]的位置則沒有。兩個月台在車站北端、樞紐以北的位置也設有一條下通道連通<ref name="ERA-Bulletin-Oct2018" />。月台現時設有灰色的工字樑柱，每隔一柱就有「世貿科特蘭」的站名牌。「世界貿易中心」的站名牌則安裝在車站牆壁上<ref name="nypost.com 2018">{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2018/08/24/subway-station-destroyed-on-9-11-finally-ready-to-reopen/|title=Subway station destroyed on 9/11 finally ready to reopen|date=August 24, 2018|website=New York Post|access-date=August 26, 2018|archive-date=2021-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210302150604/https://nypost.com/2018/08/24/subway-station-destroyed-on-9-11-finally-ready-to-reopen/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?215|title=IRT Cortlandt St/WTC station|last=|first=|date=September 28, 2001|website=nycsubway.org|publisher=New York City Transit|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210123083946/https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?215|archive-date=2021-01-23|dead-url=no|access-date=September 7, 2018}}</ref>。車站也設有空調系統<ref name=":9">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/new-york-city-subway-station-911-attack-reopens-today-after-nearly-2-decades-2018-09-08/|title=NYC subway station at site of 9/11 attack reopens after nearly 2 decades|last=|first=|date=September 8, 2018|work=CBS News|access-date=September 9, 2018|language=en|archive-date=2021-09-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210912135209/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/new-york-city-subway-station-911-attack-reopens-today-after-nearly-2-decades-2018-09-08/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2018年在此站以100萬美元裝設名為''CHORUS''的藝術品<ref name="MTA 2018">{{cite web|url=http://www.mta.info/press-release/nyc-transit/mta-opens-new-1-subway-station-world-trade-center|title=Press Release - NYC Transit - MTA Opens New 1 Subway Station at World Trade Center|date=2018-09-08|website=MTA|access-date=2018-09-10|archive-date=2021-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211224851/https://www.mta.info/press-release/nyc-transit/mta-opens-new-1-subway-station-world-trade-center|dead-url=no}}</ref>，由{{link-en|安·漢密爾頓 (藝術家)|Ann Hamilton (artist)|安·漢密爾頓}}製作，面積4350平方呎以編織為主題的藝術品。這個藝術品包括若干文件內的著名語錄，包括[[世界人權宣言|世界人權宣言]]及[[美國獨立宣言|美國獨立宣言]]的名言，雕刻在車站牆壁上<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/30/nyregion/at-cortlandt-street-subway-station-art-woven-from-words.html?_r=1|title=At Cortlandt Street Subway Station, Art Woven From Words|author=Dunlap, David|date=2015-04-28|work=The New York Times|access-date=2015-04-30|archive-date=2021-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210503141136/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/30/nyregion/at-cortlandt-street-subway-station-art-woven-from-words.html?_r=1|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nypost.com 2018" /><ref name=":9" />。

=== 出口 ===
重建的車站與[[錢伯斯街-世界貿易中心／公園廣場／科特蘭街車站|錢伯斯街-世界貿易中心／公園廣場／科特蘭街車站]]以及[[世界貿易中心車站_(PATH)|世界貿易中心的PATH車站]]連結，都是世界貿易中心交通樞紐的一部分。世貿科特蘭車站在世界貿易中心樞紐站廳（又名眼睛）以西<ref name=":4" /><ref name="nypost september 2011">{{cite news|url=https://nypost.com/2011/09/07/cortlandt-street-station-comes-back-to-life/|title=Cortlandt Street station comes back to life|author=Jennifer Fermino|date=September 7, 2011|newspaper=[[New_York_Post|New York Post]]|accessdate=April 17, 2014|publisher=New York Post|location=New York City|archive-date=2022-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108195856/https://nypost.com/2011/09/07/cortlandt-street-station-comes-back-to-life/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/10/nyregion/fulton-center-a-subway-complex-reopens-in-lower-manhattan.html|title=Fulton Center, a Subway Complex, Reopens in Lower Manhattan|last=Yee|first=Vivian|date=November 9, 2014|work=The New York Times|access-date=September 15, 2017|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2021-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028212705/https://www.nytimes.com/vi-assets/static-assets/global-2c70a72e6a867f256c6ccdf508c13728.css|dead-url=no}}</ref>。由世界貿易中心交通樞紐進入一共有4個出口<ref name="Reopening">{{cite web|url=http://www.ny1.com/nyc/all-boroughs/transit/2018/09/07/cortland-street-station-to-reopen-soon-after-17-years-manhattan-nyc-train-station-stop|title=Sources: A long-awaited Manhattan 1 train stop will reopen Saturday|last=Martinez|first=Jose|date=2018-09-07|website=Spectrum News NY1 | New York City|access-date=2018-09-07|archive-date=2021-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505204947/https://www.ny1.com/nyc/all-boroughs/transit/2018/09/07/cortland-street-station-to-reopen-soon-after-17-years-manhattan-nyc-train-station-stop|dead-url=no}}</ref>。軌道下方設兩個夾層，分別位於車站南北兩端，並可轉乘[[紐新航港局過哈德遜河捷運|PATH]]列車。北夾層可通往兩個月台，而南夾層只連往南行月台<ref name="ERA-Bulletin-Oct2018"/>。眼睛大廈上層陽台往上城月台還有額外的出口，南大堂亦然，可連往[[世界貿易中心三號大樓|世界貿易中心三號大樓]]<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|url=http://ny.curbed.com/2015/4/30/9965298/9-11-shuttered-cortlandt-st-stop-begins-road-to-reopening|title=9/11-Shuttered Cortlandt St. Stop Begins Road to Reopening|last=Alberts|first=Hana R.|date=April 30, 2015|website=Curbed NY|access-date=December 25, 2016|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108131659/https://ny.curbed.com/2015/4/30/9965298/9-11-shuttered-cortlandt-st-stop-begins-road-to-reopening|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ERA-Bulletin-Oct2018"/>。乘客可以出站經世貿樞紐前往[[福爾頓轉運中心|福爾頓轉運中心]]轉乘<ref name="nypost september 2011" />。

南行月台設有兩個出口直通地面。第一個是在月台最北端，設有升降機和樓梯到維西街，另一個是在車站最南端往科特蘭路的一對樓梯<ref name="ERA-Bulletin-Oct2018">{{cite journal | title=MTA New York City Transit Opens WTC Cortlandt Station On The 1|first=Subutay|last=Musluoglu|journal=Electric Railroaders' Association Bulletin|via=Issuu | date=October 2018 | url=https://issuu.com/erausa/docs/2018-10-bulletin | access-date=April 10, 2018|pages=1, 7|volume=61|number=10}}</ref>。車站可透過維西街的升降機[[美國殘疾人法案|無障礙通行]]，亦可透過世界貿易中心交通樞紐現有的升降機通行。車站還設有額外的升降機由月台到達下通道<ref name="MTA-CPOC-Jun2018">{{Cite web|url=http://web.mta.info/mta/news/books/pdf/180618_1330_CPOC.pdf|title=Capital Program Oversight Committee Meeting June 2018|date=June 18, 2018|publisher=[[Metropolitan_Transportation_Authority|Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]|pages=29|accessdate=June 17, 2018|archive-date=2018-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617165707/http://web.mta.info/mta/news/books/pdf/180618_1330_CPOC.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ERA-Bulletin-Oct2018"/>。

在911事件以前，車站的全天候入口位於車站北端維西街和西百老匯的交界，設有一系列[[驗票閘門|閘機]]和一部全高式轉棍閘機<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?228|title=Vesey St. entrance to Cortlandt St. station|last=|first=|date=September 28, 2001|website=nycsubway.org|publisher=New York City Transit|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210714190915/https://www.nycsubway.org/perl/show?228|archive-date=2021-07-14|dead-url=no|access-date=September 7, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nycrail.com:80/images/wtcsubway/10_10_01/irtcort2001_1008AR.JPG|title=Vesey Street Turnstile Bank|last=|first=|date=September 28, 2001|website=nycrail.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20020415120949/http://www.nycrail.com/images/wtcsubway/10_10_01/irtcort2001_1008AR.JPG|archive-date=2002-04-15|dead-url=yes|access-date=September 7, 2018}}</ref>。這個出口的詢問處在2007年車站最後拆除前仍然存在<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tribecatrib.com/content/waiting-1-train-wtc-station-open-end-next-year|title=Waiting for the #1 Train: WTC Station to Open at End of Next Year|last=Glassman|first=Carl|date=July 5, 2017|website=tribecatrib.com|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210714190920/http://tribecatrib.com/content/waiting-1-train-wtc-station-open-end-next-year|archive-date=2021-07-14|dead-url=no|access-date=September 7, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ltvsquad.com/2006/07/13/abandoned-cortlandt-station-the-911-line/|title=The Abandoned Cortlandt Street station and the 9/11 Line - LTV Squad|last=Anastasio|first=Joseph|date=July 13, 2006|website=ltvsquad.com|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915020127/http://ltvsquad.com/2006/07/13/abandoned-cortlandt-station-the-911-line/|archive-date=2019-09-15|dead-url=no|access-date=September 7, 2018}}</ref>。往世界貿易中心大堂的入口<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.labelscar.com/new-york/mall-at-world-trade-center|title=The Mall at the World Trade Center; New York, New York - Labelscar: The Retail History Blog|last=|first=|date=September 11, 2006|work=Labelscar: The Retail History Blog|access-date=September 7, 2018|language=en-US|archive-date=2014-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006065841/http://www.labelscar.com/new-york/mall-at-world-trade-center|dead-url=no}}</ref>包括各月台中央設有全高式轉棍閘機<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/news/1m-a-day-fix-wtc-subway-article-1.485744|title=$1M-A-Day Fix For WTC Subway|last=Gittrich|first=Greg|date=January 16, 2002|work=New York Daily News|access-date=September 7, 2018|last2=Donohue|first2=Pete|pages=18–19|language=en|archive-date=2019-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212141416/https://www.nydailynews.com/archives/news/1m-a-day-fix-wtc-subway-article-1.485744|dead-url=no}}</ref>，並只在平日早上6時40分至晚上10時開放<ref name=":5">{{Cite web|url=http://www.columbia.edu/~brennan/abandoned/cortlandt.html|title=Cortlandt St|last=Brennan|first=Joseph|date=2002-05-03|website=Abandoned Stations|access-date=2017-09-15|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109015802/http://www.columbia.edu/~brennan/abandoned/cortlandt.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{Efn|The hours can be seen in the following video at the 0:52 mark on the door.<ref>{{Citation|last=NYCSubwaySystem|title=NYC Subway: Cortlandt Street, World Trade Center, 19 Trains|date=1997|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IVJDC_jLeFo|volume=|pages=|access-date=September 7, 2018|archive-date=2020-09-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200926085310/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IVJDC_jLeFo|dead-url=no}}</ref>}}。車站的南端設有通過世界貿易中心四號大樓往自由街的出口<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mta.nyc.ny.us:80/nyct/maps/mapdown1028.pdf|title=Lower Manhattan Subways & Buses as of Sun 10/28 3 pm|last=|first=|date=October 28, 2001|website=mta.nyc.ny.us|publisher=Metropolitan Transportation Authority|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20011109020322/http://www.mta.nyc.ny.us/nyct/maps/mapdown1028.pdf|archive-date=2001-11-09|dead-url=yes|access-date=September 7, 2018}}</ref>。

